39
00:05:19,119 --> 00:05:22,155
   

40
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:23,315
   

41
00:05:27,759 --> 00:05:29,899
 - Reporting.  
 - Come in!

42
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:38,879
You put out the fire at Wufang Street.

43
00:05:38,879 --> 00:05:40,779
You made a meritorious achievement.

44
00:05:45,399 --> 00:05:47,720
These tea leaves look pretty good. How come I haven't seen it before?

45
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,220
Put it down!

46
00:05:51,451 --> 00:05:52,986
Get over here!

47
00:05:56,539 --> 00:05:58,325
Forget the tea leaves.

48
00:05:58,325 --> 00:06:01,527
Forget all the commendations or recognitions, you can put them aside.

49
00:06:02,199 --> 00:06:04,610
I just received three complaints.

50
00:06:04,610 --> 00:06:06,889
Three!

51
00:06:07,759 --> 00:06:11,759
The first one, the associated organizations complained that

52
00:06:11,759 --> 00:06:12,879
you were uncooperative.

53
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:15,079
You were brusque and rough.

54
00:06:15,079 --> 00:06:16,000
Second!

55
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,120
The general public complained about your bad attitude

56
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:22,020
and that you damaged his car.

57
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:23,040
Third.

58
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:28,079
Your peers complained that you disregarded the instructor's orders.

59
00:06:28,079 --> 00:06:30,121
You were uncooperative, had a bad attitude, and you didn't obey your instructor.

60
00:06:30,121 --> 00:06:31,439
You...

61
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:32,959
Aren't you...

62
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:36,040
Aren't you going to explain yourself?

63
00:06:37,150 --> 00:06:39,360
The car should be removed. That person deserves to be beaten.

64
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,702
If I'm incompetent, I deserve a reprimand.

65
00:06:41,702 --> 00:06:45,021
If you don't like me, just reassign me elsewhere.

66
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,519
Do you think I don't dare?

67
00:06:49,519 --> 00:06:52,240
You keep making trouble for me every now and then.

68
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:55,079
Every month, there's something new.

69
00:06:55,079 --> 00:06:57,000
Division Chief Gao.

70
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,789
You tell me!

71
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:01,399
Division Chief Gao, don't get worked up.

72
00:07:01,399 --> 00:07:02,959
I've looked into the situation.

73
00:07:02,959 --> 00:07:05,240
The situation was dire.

74
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:08,319
Comrade Song Yan and the comrades from Wufang Fire Station

75
00:07:08,319 --> 00:07:10,879
had a bit of a disagreement on the plan of action.

76
00:07:10,879 --> 00:07:16,003
They went ahead with Song Yan's method and managed to prevent the fire from spreading.

77
00:07:16,003 --> 00:07:17,938
Regarding the car removal,

78
00:07:17,938 --> 00:07:22,179
they couldn't reach the owner of the car who parked his car on a fire exit.

79
00:07:22,179 --> 00:07:24,969
Song Yan handled it that way to ensure they reached the fire as quickly as possible

80
00:07:24,969 --> 00:07:28,749
and to minimize damages to the public's well-being and property, am I right?

81
00:07:29,616 --> 00:07:33,600
You always come up with all sorts of reasons to cover him.

82
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,759
Division Chief Gao, you always say this.

83
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:37,639
"The scene of a fire is like a battlefield."

84
00:07:37,639 --> 00:07:40,279
There are many variables working on the frontline.

85
00:07:40,279 --> 00:07:43,439
It's hard to please everyone.

86
00:07:44,199 --> 00:07:48,200
If Song Yan hadn't insisted on going ahead with his team,

87
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:52,539
the little boy and girl wouldn't have been saved.

88
00:07:54,753 --> 00:07:58,619
Fine. I won't pursue the other two complaints.

89
00:07:58,619 --> 00:08:01,900
As for the removal of the car, that's clearly a bad image for our firefighters.

90
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,079
It has to be resolved.

91
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:05,360
Yes! Make him write a report!

92
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,720
I submitted one last time. You want me to write another?

93
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,600
That means it was not good enough.

94
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,419
Do it again.

95
00:08:11,419 --> 00:08:12,392
Write it!

96
00:08:12,392 --> 00:08:14,094
Three thousand words!

97
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,639
Not a word less.

98
00:08:16,639 --> 00:08:18,780
For every word you miss

99
00:08:18,780 --> 00:08:20,610
you will be fined ¥1,000  (~$140) .

100
00:08:26,179 --> 00:08:27,679
Song Yan!

101
00:08:29,739 --> 00:08:31,439
Song Yan!

102
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:37,120
I heard that a couple of gas tanks exploded at the scene.

103
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,252
It was precarious.

104
00:08:39,252 --> 00:08:40,654
I'm not nagging at you,

105
00:08:40,654 --> 00:08:44,220
but can you not be so reckless when something happens?

106
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:47,019
Saving lives is important, but don't neglect your own safety.

107
00:08:47,019 --> 00:08:50,359
Now, I get anxious whenever your team goes on a mission.

108
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:53,080
Thanks for your concern, Boss.

109
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,440
I'm leaving.

110
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,640
I...

111
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:07,300
That new doctor, Xu Qin, is pretty amazing.

112
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:10,039
I heard she will be getting the spot on the research team.

113
00:09:10,039 --> 00:09:11,159
Based on what?

114
00:09:11,159 --> 00:09:13,039
Just because she studied in the US?

115
00:09:13,039 --> 00:09:17,119
She's still a rookie. Does she have the experience?

116
00:09:17,119 --> 00:09:18,759
That's why she was assigned to the ER.

117
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:21,000
After some time, she'd be put on the research team.

118
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:25,519
It may not seem justified, but you can't really name any problems.

119
00:09:25,519 --> 00:09:26,733
I guess it's a special admission.

120
00:09:26,733 --> 00:09:30,879
In my opinion, it's about time for you to get the spot.

121
00:09:30,879 --> 00:09:33,240
You're older than her and more experienced.

122
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:36,476
But unfortunately, she has backing.

123
00:09:36,476 --> 00:09:39,012
If you need backing for that spot, then everyone should go find one.

124
00:09:39,012 --> 00:09:41,320
Who doesn't have connections and backgrounds?

125
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:43,360
Her background is special, though.

126
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:45,279
I heard her last name is Meng.

127
00:09:45,279 --> 00:09:48,420
She changed it in order to keep a low profile.

128
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:50,480
Meng? And the name?

129
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,559
Guo Kun Group.

130
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:52,879
For real?

131
00:09:52,879 --> 00:09:54,480
Her dad is Meng Huaijin?

132
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,919
That's what her profile said.

133
00:09:55,919 --> 00:09:59,199
I saw it when I was processing her onboarding.

134
00:09:59,199 --> 00:10:03,759
So the handsome and aristocratic guy who picks her up from work every day

135
00:10:03,759 --> 00:10:05,879
is the young master of Guo Kun Group?

136
00:10:05,879 --> 00:10:09,399
So she's untouchable, and has car services every day.

137
00:10:09,399 --> 00:10:14,474
 The thought of having to work with a person who relies on connections frustrates me. 

138
00:10:22,722 --> 00:10:24,958
If you don't want to work with me,

139
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:27,427
I can talk to the management for you.

140
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,800
Should I?

141
00:10:47,470 --> 00:10:49,500
   

142
00:10:52,919 --> 00:10:54,519
Brother!

143
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:00,120
You got a new car?

144
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:02,600
It's your car.

145
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,899
I got it for you.

146
00:11:03,899 --> 00:11:06,220
What do you think? Do you like it?

147
00:11:06,220 --> 00:11:08,300
Director Meng, your taste is getting better.

148
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,859
What can I do?

149
00:11:09,859 --> 00:11:12,679
You won't go home and you don't allow the chauffeur to drive you.

150
00:11:12,679 --> 00:11:15,399
Mom worries about your commute.

151
00:11:15,399 --> 00:11:19,270
Give it a try. I'll change it if you don't like it.

152
00:11:21,519 --> 00:11:23,019
Thanks.

153
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:52,039
The road ahead is closed due to an accident inside the tunnel.

154
00:11:52,039 --> 00:11:53,619
Please take another route.

155
00:11:53,619 --> 00:11:55,679
Okay. Is anyone injured?

156
00:11:55,679 --> 00:11:57,039
The car got badly smashed.

157
00:11:57,039 --> 00:11:58,960
I presume the driver is hurt pretty badly.

158
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:01,500
The ambulance will be here soon. Please don't block the road.

159
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,519
- Got it. 
 - Thanks for your cooperation.

160
00:12:13,132 --> 00:12:14,868
You're off duty.

161
00:12:14,868 --> 00:12:17,559
But I'm still a doctor.

162
00:12:17,559 --> 00:12:19,819
The ambulance will be here soon.

163
00:12:19,819 --> 00:12:22,000
The longer we wait, the more dangerous it is for the victim.

164
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,700
Brother.

165
00:12:24,519 --> 00:12:26,059
Stay safe.

166
00:12:36,289 --> 00:12:37,220
Hey there.

167
00:12:37,220 --> 00:12:39,880
I'm a doctor. Do you need assistance?

168
00:12:44,249 --> 00:12:47,279
I have a doctor here who can help. Should I let her in?

169
00:12:47,279 --> 00:12:48,700
 Let her through. 

170
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:49,712
Got it.

171
00:12:49,712 --> 00:12:51,412
Come with me.

172
00:13:16,639 --> 00:13:18,240
The ambulance is finally here.

173
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:21,720
We won't trouble you then.

174
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,836
It's no trouble.

175
00:13:22,836 --> 00:13:24,236
Thank you.

176
00:14:25,399 --> 00:14:27,199
Move it away.

177
00:14:37,159 --> 00:14:38,759
Lift him up.

178
00:15:14,403 --> 00:15:17,383
Instructor, the vice captain is not here yet?

179
00:15:17,383 --> 00:15:20,260
No, he's on duty at the station.

180
00:15:20,260 --> 00:15:23,023
Good work, guys! Come grab some food.

181
00:15:23,023 --> 00:15:24,519
Five minutes!

182
00:15:24,519 --> 00:15:26,639
Take turns to eat.

183
00:15:33,432 --> 00:15:36,671
You can't eat because of your toothache. Drink some soup instead.

184
00:15:45,607 --> 00:15:47,007
How is it?

185
00:15:47,759 --> 00:15:49,359
Are you feeling better?

186
00:15:59,759 --> 00:16:02,159
You went back and came out again?

187
00:16:02,159 --> 00:16:05,380
I just want you to eat up and go back to rest early.

188
00:16:10,937 --> 00:16:12,437
   

189
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:23,320
Hello?

190
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:24,679
I've eaten.

191
00:16:24,679 --> 00:16:27,019
We had a mission to carry out today.

192
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:31,559
I know.

193
00:16:31,559 --> 00:16:33,759
I'll hurry up.

194
00:16:33,759 --> 00:16:36,619
The approval for the detachment has to follow procedures.

195
00:16:36,619 --> 00:16:39,579
Give me a bit more time, okay?

196
00:16:41,239 --> 00:16:42,539
Let's talk later.

197
00:17:01,799 --> 00:17:03,559
Are you hiding something from me?

198
00:17:03,559 --> 00:17:05,500
No, nothing.

199
00:17:07,279 --> 00:17:09,079
We sleep and eat together every day.

200
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:12,951
Do you think I wouldn't notice something is wrong?

201
00:17:12,951 --> 00:17:15,799
I think you're thinking too much.

202
00:17:15,799 --> 00:17:17,080
Fine.

203
00:17:17,080 --> 00:17:18,559
I won't ask.

204
00:17:18,559 --> 00:17:21,019
You can tell me when you're ready.

205
00:17:53,606 --> 00:17:56,000
   

206
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,744
 For the Emergency Department, 
   

207
00:17:57,744 --> 00:18:01,000
there has to be at least one professional training a week. 
    

208
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:06,119
We will focus on the treatment of critically ill patients.

209
00:18:06,119 --> 00:18:09,119
For example, basic rescue techniques in treating

210
00:18:09,119 --> 00:18:12,519
acute heart attacks, strokes,

211
00:18:12,519 --> 00:18:14,459
shocks, and others.

212
00:18:14,459 --> 00:18:19,200
So while you are expected to carry out your responsibilities,

213
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:22,960
we have to establish strong teamwork.

214
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:25,839
In order to increase the success rate of emergency care

215
00:18:25,839 --> 00:18:29,000
by administering precise treatment, the department has decided

216
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:33,279
to separate the Red Zone into A and B, two emergency response teams.

217
00:18:33,279 --> 00:18:37,720
Based on the type of patients, we'll carry out the treatment according to the conditions.

218
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:38,851
Do you understand?

219
00:18:38,851 --> 00:18:40,119
 Yes. 

220
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:43,359
Yellow Zone and Green Zone may go.

221
00:18:43,359 --> 00:18:44,480
Conduct your rounds.

222
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:46,180
Red Zone, please stay back.

223
00:18:52,799 --> 00:18:55,880
We have decided to separate Red Zone into two teams.

224
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:57,839
For Team A,

225
00:18:57,839 --> 00:18:59,759
Yang Sijia will be in charge.

226
00:18:59,759 --> 00:19:00,799
Okay.

227
00:19:00,799 --> 00:19:04,000
For Team B, Xu Qin will be in charge.

228
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,240
You're free to choose your own team members.

229
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:07,480
I'll leave that to you.

230
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:09,500
It will benefit your operations.

231
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:10,680
Okay?

232
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:12,559
Department Chief, I'll go to Team A.

233
00:19:12,559 --> 00:19:14,720
Department Chief, I'll join Team A, too.

234
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:16,319
Department Chief, I also want to join Team A.

235
00:19:16,319 --> 00:19:18,259
Count me in, Department Chief.

236
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:24,759
Department Chief, that means my team is full.

237
00:19:34,839 --> 00:19:36,739
Let's go with that, then.

238
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:48,160
- Dr. Xu. 
 - Dr. Xu.

239
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:50,039
- Let's do the best we can. 
  - Do our best! 

240
00:19:50,039 --> 00:19:51,739
Get to work.

241
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:55,300
Get to work.

242
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,800
Get to work.

243
00:19:59,839 --> 00:20:01,200
Gear up.

244
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,000
Ready!

245
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:30,839
Report! I'm done!

246
00:20:30,839 --> 00:20:31,840
Report! I'm done!

247
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:34,240
- Report! I'm done! 
 - Report! I'm done!

248
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:35,160
Zhan Dapeng!

249
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:36,279
Pi Shaojie!

250
00:20:36,279 --> 00:20:37,319
Tang Jie!

251
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:38,359
You failed!

252
00:20:38,359 --> 00:20:39,960
You three. Take everything off and start over.

253
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:40,741
Got it!

254
00:20:40,741 --> 00:20:42,442
Yes, Sir.

255
00:20:44,579 --> 00:20:46,259
Ready. Focus!

256
00:20:57,839 --> 00:21:00,640
- Report! Done! 
 - Report! Done!

257
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:02,563
You failed!

258
00:21:02,563 --> 00:21:06,582
Captain, I put everything on according to the squad leader's instructions.

259
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:14,060
Is it secured?

260
00:21:14,060 --> 00:21:17,799
When you enter the fire scene, your breathing apparatus might get snatched. Do you know that?

261
00:21:18,599 --> 00:21:21,720
Captain, somebody is going to steal my breathing apparatus?

262
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:23,440
Have you not heard of people trying to save someone from drowning

263
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:26,079
but ended up drowning themselves due to being dragged by the victims?

264
00:21:26,079 --> 00:21:28,279
Firefighters have lost their lives because of that.

265
00:21:28,279 --> 00:21:31,059
Make sure you wear your breathing apparatus securely.

266
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:36,340
There's something called instinct

267
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:40,179
in human nature.

268
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:15,080
Gather around.

269
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:24,279
If your dream is to become a firefighter, step forward.

270
00:22:24,279 --> 00:22:25,879
Form a line.

271
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:35,160
I want to hear the truth.

272
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:36,759
Why do you want to be a firefighter?

273
00:22:36,759 --> 00:22:39,240
Report, Captain! Because I want to save lives!

274
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:40,839
I want to save the common people!

275
00:22:40,839 --> 00:22:44,359
Report, Captain! I think firefighters are the greatest!

276
00:22:44,359 --> 00:22:48,700
Report, Captain! I think being a firefighter is an honorable occupation!

277
00:22:53,039 --> 00:22:55,440
Is that what you really think?

278
00:22:56,680 --> 00:23:00,079
A few days ago, in the Wufang Street fire,

279
00:23:00,079 --> 00:23:02,640
I received complaints.

280
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:05,484
The fire station got complaints, too.

281
00:23:05,484 --> 00:23:07,279
Some people said

282
00:23:07,279 --> 00:23:09,955
that our attitude was bad while maintaining the crowd in order at the scene.

283
00:23:09,955 --> 00:23:14,560
Last month, Yang Chi and his team saved a kid in the sewer.

284
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:16,160
They were covered in filth.

285
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:18,799
The stench lingered even after three days.

286
00:23:18,799 --> 00:23:19,680
Jiang Yi.

287
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:21,880
He left his mom and is away from home.

288
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:25,799
Because of his duties, he hasn't gone home to see her in two years.

289
00:23:25,799 --> 00:23:28,580
After hearing these stories,

290
00:23:28,580 --> 00:23:30,739
do you still wish to be here?

291
00:23:32,279 --> 00:23:34,879
Are you happy to put on this gear?

292
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:42,230
The firefighting gear is not as comfortable as you think!

293
00:23:42,230 --> 00:23:43,699
Complaints.

294
00:23:43,699 --> 00:23:45,100
Grievances.

295
00:23:45,100 --> 00:23:47,659
No one understands the efforts you put in.

296
00:23:48,963 --> 00:23:51,523
It's part and parcel of being a firefighter.

297
00:23:52,799 --> 00:23:55,079
But why are there still hundreds of thousands of firefighters

298
00:23:55,079 --> 00:24:01,680
who dashes out at the first sound of the alarm, 365 days a year, 24 hours a day?

299
00:24:11,119 --> 00:24:12,900
Take a look.

300
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:17,089
Tell me.

301
00:24:17,089 --> 00:24:19,000
What do you see?

302
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:22,328
I see the bustling streets of the city.

303
00:24:22,328 --> 00:24:26,160
I see towering buildings and parks.

304
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:29,386
I see residential buildings filled with warmth.

305
00:24:29,386 --> 00:24:31,300
I hope

306
00:24:31,300 --> 00:24:33,480
you have a clear view

307
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:35,351
and a clear understanding.

308
00:24:36,039 --> 00:24:39,060
Why do we train so hard every day?

309
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:47,280
It is to protect people's everyday lives.

310
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,119
 Hurry up, will you? 

311
00:25:25,119 --> 00:25:26,979
 Wait up. 

312
00:25:38,959 --> 00:25:41,780
 Song Yan, this is vandalism. 

313
00:25:42,559 --> 00:25:43,599
 It's fine. 

314
00:25:43,599 --> 00:25:46,972
 This wall is part of the cultural corner on Wufang Street. Graffiti is fine. 

315
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:52,839
 Well? How is it? 

316
00:25:53,799 --> 00:25:56,259
 Look at what you wrote. 

317
00:25:56,259 --> 00:25:58,280
 You don't get it? 

318
00:25:59,319 --> 00:26:02,739
 If you smile, 

319
00:26:02,739 --> 00:26:05,480
 the son city. 

320
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:09,979
 If you smile, the sun fills the city. 

